h3#overview Overview
p
	| Chico Mesh provides a set of CSS columns that makes the laying out of a website easy and fast. It isn't part of the CSS core, that's why you have to download the file and reference it on your HTML document.
form.container(action="/versions/#{latest.version}/chico-mesh.css")
	input.ch-btn.ch-primary(type="submit", value="Download Chico Mesh")

h3#classnames Classnames
p
	| Each column is expressed in fractions that represent a width percent of our content.
p
	| The classnames replace the bar ( / ) in the fraction by a dash ( - ):
ul.ch-list
	li
		code 50%
		|  same as 
		code 1/2
		|  same as 
		code .ch-g1-2
		| .
	li
		code 75%
		|  same as 
		code 3/4
		|  same as
		code .ch-g3-4
		| .
	li
		code 20%
		|  same as 
		code 1/5
		|  same as
		code .ch-g1-5
		| .

h3#gutters Gutters
p
	| The grids have neither padding nor margin. To be able to get the gutters, you have to assign a margin 
	strong to the element that's inside the grid
	| . For that, we defined 3 classes that create a 10px margin to the inner element:
ul.ch-list
	li
		code .ch-leftcolumn
		| : assign it to the left element.
	li
		code .ch-centercolumn
		| : assign it to the center element.
	li
		code .ch-rightcolumn
		| : assign it to the right element.

h3#rounding Rounding
p
	| The 1/3 and 1/6 column widths have infinite or too long decimals. To fix this issue, we created a grid with the extra percent you need to round to 100%.
ul.ch-list
	li
		code 33.34%
		|  same as
		code 1/3
		|  same as
		code .ch-g1-3r
		| .
	li
		code 16.66%
		|  same as
		code 1/6
		|  same as
		code .ch-g1-6r
		| .
p
	| If you need 3 columns of equal widths, one of the 3 grids have to be 
	code ch-g1-3r
	| , like this:
pre
	| <div class="ch-g1-3">
	| 	<div class="ch-box ch-leftcolumn">
	| 		33,33%
	| 	</div>
	| </div>
	| <div class="ch-g1-3r">
	| 	<div class="ch-box ch-centercolumn">
	| 		33,34%
	| 	</div>
	| </div>
	| <div class="ch-g1-3">
	| 	<div class="ch-box ch-rightcolumn">
	| 		33,33%
	| 	</div>
	| </div> 
p
	| Same thing happens with 1/6: one of the 6 grids have to be 
	code ch-g1-6r
	| .
p
	| If for some reason, you need to clear the floats, you can use the 
	code clearfix
	|  class defined on core.css:
pre
	| <div class="ch-g1-4">
	| 	<div class="ch-box ch-leftcolumn">
	| 		Left 1/4
	| 	</div>
	| </div>
	| <div class="ch-g2-4">
	| 	<div class="ch-box ch-centercolumn">
	| 		Center 2/4
	| 	</div>
	| </div>
	| <div class="ch-g1-4">
	| 	<div class="ch-box ch-rightcolumn">
	| 		Right 1/4
	| 	</div>
	| </div>
	| 
	| <div class="clearfix"></div>

